author: Benjamin Steward
reviewBody: Two words can express the best item on the secret menu. Not many people know this, but you have to try the alfredo shake. Grab a cup and go up to the pasta place and ask for some alfredo sauce in your cup. Then got to the ice cream place and get two scoops of bunny tracks or scooper hero. The workers might look like they think you're insane, but trust me, they get this requested several times on a good day.

author: Nick Steffensmeier
reviewBody: This is the best place to eat on ISU campus. During the day when food is all you can eat you can have as much fancy coffee that you want. They have spot that serves Starbucks like drinks. The only drinks they don't server are blended ice drinks; which is fine by me. Also, there food selection is great. They have a sandwich of the day that is always delicious. Overall, if it are going to eat on campus eat at conversation. Not everyone can find where it is, but once found you know you will want to go back. Of course this is not the best place in town, far from it; but, this is the best place to eat if living on campus and purchased meal bundles

author: Danny Stein
reviewBody: Conversations does it better than Seasons, depending on your tongue. For me it hits a little better. They are way more consistent in the service category, where I get actual words from the employees who work diligently in the kitchen. They also have a couple of superior options to Seasons across the street, however the size proportions and quality can be inconsistent. I think the one thing that has me most scratching my head is why they would decide to have it be a get & go only location. In summation, I think Conversations is still one of the weaker options, but at least you can always be serviced for get & go, unlike West Side Market.

author: Hannah
reviewBody: Generally, I love ISU food, but not conversations. I guess it used to be good. 1st time there, decent enough burger but that was the only good thing about it. Not sit down, gotta walk across street to sit down and eat. My side was cilantro lime rice which I usually enjoy at other food places, but it tasted old/weird and entirely lacking flavor. Even the rice had a weird/old texture. Also is awkward trying to see the food in order to know what you want. Food is covered which I get but very little pictures or displays of food options.
